    <chapter id="BrazierHoarding">
        <section>
            <page_title>
                <title>Brazier of Hoarding</title>
            </page_title>
            <p align="center"><stack item="arcanearchives:brazier_of_hoarding" scale="3.0"/></p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                A Brazier of Hoarding is an organization device that can act as a drop-off point to store items in your <link ref="Networks">Network</link>. Braziers of Hoarding are also a light source.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_trove"/> Any items used on, or dropped on top of, a Brazier of Hoarding will be transported to a <link ref="RadiantTrove">Radiant Trove</link> that contains the item.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_chest"/> If no appropriate Radiant Troves exist in your network, items will be placed in <link ref="RadiantChest">Radiant Chests</link>, starting with chests that already contain an instance of the item.
            </p>
            <p>
                If no storage can be found, items are ejected from the Brazier of Hoarding.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_sceptermanipulation"/> Using a <link ref="ScepterManipulation">Scepter of Manipulation</link> on a Brazier of Hoarding will toggle whether it is allowed to place items in Radiant Chests that don't already contain a copy of the item.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:gemcutters_table"/> Braziers of Hoarding can be crafted on a <link ref="GemCuttersTable">Gem Cutter's Table</link>.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p italics="true">
                ...Lore fragment TBD
            </p>
        </section>
    </chapter>

