    <chapter id="RadiantChest">
        <section>
            <page_title>
                <title>Radiant Chest</title>
            </page_title>
            <p align="center"><stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_chest" scale="3.0"/></p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                Radiant Chests are a storage container with as many slots as a vanilla double chest in a single block. Each slot of a Radiant Chest can store up to 256 items instead of the stored item’s normal stack limit.
            </p>
            <p>
                At the bottom of a Radiant Chest’s interface, you can give it a name to help keep your storage organized. Radiant Chests are also a light source.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_manifest"/> Items stored in Radiant Chests appear on a <link ref="Manifest">Manifest</link> as long as the Chest's chunk is loaded.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_scepterrevelation"/> Using a <link ref="ScepterRevelation">Scepter of Revelation</link> on a Radiant Chest will return the chest's name, and how many slots of its inventory are available.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_rawquartz"/> Radiant Chests can be crafted by using a piece of <link ref="RadiantQuartz">Raw Radiant Quartz</link> on a chest while sneaking. Any items inside the chest will be imported, and if used on a double vanilla chest, both chests' inventories will be imported into the new Radiant Chest.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="minecraft:crafting_table"/> Radiant Chests can be crafted conventionally.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <recipe type="shaped">
                <recipe.result>
                    <stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_chest"/>
                </recipe.result>
            </recipe>
            <space height="8"/>
            <horizontal_rule/>
