    <chapter id="RadiantCraftingTable">
        <section>
            <page_title>
                <title>Radiant Crafting Table</title>
            </page_title>
            <p align="center"><stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_crafting_table" scale="3.0"/></p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                A Radiant Crafting Table acts as a conventional crafting table, except items are not dropped when you leave the interface. Radiant Crafting Tables are also a light source.
            </p>
            <p>
                After crafting an item, you can click on one of the slots on the right side of the interface to save the recipe. If enough items are present in your inventory, clicking on a slot with a saved recipe crafts the item without requiring you to set items on the crafting grid. Shift clicking clears the recipe in a slot.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_scepterrevelation"/> Using a <link ref="ScepterRevelation">Scepter of Revelation</link> on a Radiant Crafting Table will return what items are present in the crafting grid.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_rawquartz"/> Radiant Crafting Tables can be crafted by using a piece of <link ref="RadiantQuartz">Raw Radiant Quartz</link> on a vanilla crafting table while sneaking.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="minecraft:crafting_table"/> Radiant Crafting Tables can be crafted conventionally.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <recipe type="shaped">
                <recipe.result>
                    <stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_crafting_table"/>
                </recipe.result>
            </recipe>
            <space height="8"/>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p italics="true">
                ...Lore fragment TBD
            </p>
        </section>
    </chapter>

    <chapter id="RadiantResonator">
        <section>
            <page_title>
                <title>Radiant Resonator</title>
            </page_title>
            <p align="center"><stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_resonator" scale="3.0"/></p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                A Radiant Resonator produces a cluster of Raw Radiant Quartz in the block above itself once every five minutes. Once Quartz is produced, the process halts until the block above the Resonator is cleared.
            </p>
            <p>
                You can only place up to three Radiant Resonators. Any further Resonators you attempt to place will pop off, and any Resonators placed by automated means will destroy themselves.
            </p>
            <p>
                Radiant Resonators only run while you’re online, even if the chunk is loaded.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_scepterrevelation"/> Using a <link ref="ScepterRevelation">Scepter of Revelation</link> on a Radiant Resonator will return its current process, and whether it is running or not..
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="minecraft:crafting_table"/> Radiant Resonators can be crafted conventionally.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <recipe type="shaped">
                <recipe.result>
                    <stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_resonator"/>
                </recipe.result>
            </recipe>
            <space height="8"/>
