    <chapter id="RadiantTank">
        <section>
            <page_title>
                <title>Radiant Tank</title>
            </page_title>
            <p align="center"><stack item="arcanearchives:radiant_tank" scale="3.0"/></p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                A Radiant Tank is a storage container that can contain up to 16 buckets of a single type of fluid. Using a Radiant Tank on a fluid inventory will transfer the target's fluid inventory into the held Radiant Tank.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_radiantamphora"/> <link ref="RadiantAmphora">Radiant Amphorae</link> can fill and empty a Radiant Tank from anywhere, as long as the tank is in a loaded chunk.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_component_containmentfield"/> By using a <link ref="ContainmentField">Containment Field</link> while sneaking, the maximum capacity can be increased by 16 buckets. Up to 9 such upgrades can be applied total.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_scepterrevelation"/> Using a <link ref="ScepterRevelation">Scepter of Revelation</link> on a Radiant Tank will return what type of fluid is stored, its current and maximum capacity, and how many upgrades have been installed.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_sceptermanipulation"/> Using a <link ref="ScepterManipulation">Scepter of Manipulation</link> on a Radiant Tank will remove one installed upgrade, so long as the storage that upgrade provided is currently unused.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:gemcutters_table" /> Radiant Tanks can be crafted on a <link ref="GemCuttersTable">Gem Cutter's Table</link>.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p italics="true">
                ...Lore fragment TBD
            </p>
        </section>
    </chapter>

