    <chapter id="Networks">
        <section>
            <page_title>
                <title>Networks</title>
            </page_title>
            <p align="center"><image src="arcanearchives:gui/guidebook/networks" tw="16" th="16" scale="3.0"/></p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p>
                Every Arcane Archives block you place becomes part of a network. Each block in the network can be accessed by certain items and devices, and ultimately ties back to you. The creation of a network is automatic, and you can only ever belong to one network.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_letterofinvitation"/> By using a <link ref="LetterInvitation">Letter of Invitation</link> given to you by another player, you can form a hybrid network with that player, pooling your resources together. Everything in both players' networks is mutually accessible.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_letterofresignation"/> By using a <link ref="LetterResignation">Letter of Resignation</link>, you can break from a hybrid network. All blocks that you placed return to your individual network.
            </p>
            <p>
                <stack item="arcanearchives:item_manifest"/> <link ref="Manifest">Manifests</link> display the contents of all inventories that are part of the network you belong to.
            </p>
            <horizontal_rule/>
            <p italics="true">
                ...Lore fragment TBD
            </p>
        </section>
    </chapter>

